==================================================
==================================================
||  		      READ ME		        ||
==================================================
==================================================
|   This is a step-by-step on creating the       |
|   rules to allow the VGA2USB devices to gain   |
|   permissions, in turn allowing screen	 |
|   capture to work.                   	         |
 ------------------------------------------------

==================================================
STEPS:
--------------------------------------------------
=================
1. Script Set-up
=================

1.1) Open Terminal and navigate to PAOL-CODE folder.

1.2) Create a directory titled "permissionsScript"
     and enter it

1.3) Create a file named "chmodBash"
       Type into terminal:
            -----------------------
	   |	                   |
	   |   $ emacs chmodBash   |
	   |   	       		   |
	    -----------------------
     ## File has no extension on purpose

1.4) Type and save into File:
            ----------------------------------
    	   |                                  |	
	   |   #!/bin/bash		      |
	   |				      |
 	   |   sudo chmod 777 /dev/vga2usb*   |
	   |				      |
	    ----------------------------------

1.5) Change permissions on chmodBash file to only executable
       Type into Terminal:
       	    --------------------------------
	   |		                    |
	   |   $ sudo chmod 001 chmodBash   |
	   |   	    	      		    |
	    -------------------------------- 

===================
2. Rule assignment
===================

2.1) Navigate to udev rules
       Type into Terminal:
       	    -----------------------------------
   	   |				       |
	   |   $ cd			       |
	   |   $ cd /etc/udev/rules.d	       |
    	   |   $ sudo emacs 85-my_rule.rules   |
	   |	       	     		       |
	    -----------------------------------
     ## Make sure file is named so, if
     	name is taken already in directory,
	85-*.rules where * is any appropriate
	name that will suffice.

2.2) Type and save into File:
            -----------------------------------------------------------
           |							       |
	   |   ACTION=="add", \					       |
	   |   SUBSYSTEM=="usb", \				       |
	   |   ATTRS{idVendor}=="5555", \			       |
 	   |   RUN+="/home/paol/paol-code/permissionsScript/chmodBash" |
	   |   							       |
	    -----------------------------------------------------------
  
2.3) Close any emacs windows not already closed

2.4) Reload udev rules
       Type in Terminal:
       	    -------------------------------------
	   |					 |
	   |   $ sudo /etc/init.d/udev restart   |
	   |   	      		       		 |
	    -------------------------------------

     ## You may be prompted with a warning, 
     	but it will work anyway. 

       
========
3. TEST
========

3.1) Navigate to /dev
       Type into Teminal:
      	    ---------------
           |               |
           |   $ cd /dev   |
           |               |
            ---------------

3.2) Plug in VGA2USB device. 
       If device is already plugged in, unplug and replug.

3.3) Check permissions on VGA2USB device
       Type into Terminal:
            -------------
           |             |   
           |   $ ls -l   |
           |             |
            -------------
      
     ## VGA2USB device should look like this everytime you plug it in:  
      crwxrwxrwx  1 root root    180,   0 Jul  9 13:55 vga2usb0
